            <li>Yivliminare Mosque</li>
            
        </ul>
        <h2><em>TURKEY IS THE WORLD’S LARGEST PRODUCER OF HAZELNUTS</em></h2>
        <p>There are a number of products synonymous with Turkey, most famously Turkish delight and coffee. What people may not realize is that Turkey produces the largest proportion of the world’s hazelnuts.<br>

In total, Turkey grows around 73% of all hazelnuts which are exported around the globe to make treats such as praline and chocolate and hazelnut spreads.</p>

<h2>TURKEY’S NATIONAL SPORT IS OIL WRESTLING</h2>

<p>Oil wrestling, also known as grease wrestling, is Turkey’s national sport. Participants coat their bodies with olive oil as they try to pin their opponent to the ground or lift them into the air.<br>

Kirkpinar Oil Wrestling Festival, in the Turkish city of Edirne,  holds the Guinness Book of Records title for the longest consecutively held sporting events. It started back in the mid-1300s and continues to take place each June, spread across 7 days. Food, dancing, and music accompany the contests.</p>
<h2>Weather</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Average winter daytime temperature: 14 – 17ºC</li>
    <li>Average summer daytime temperature: 30 – 34ºC</li>
</ul>
